summary: A dispatch-expression dispatches an invocation of a static method or function.
details: Remember: A function is technically a static method.
Return Type: return-type of the selected method overload
Return The value returned by the invoked method is returned..
checks: The type specified by module must exist.
The type specified by module must be accessible.
The type of each argument must be either a primitive-type or a reference-type.
None of the accessible method overloads will accept the given arguments.
The return-types of the applicable methods must be the same.
